<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-06-08T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-06-08T20:00:00-05:00" n="601" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/6248: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-06-09T09:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">June 9,
                                        1925—9 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 9—3:46
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>212. My 205, June 6, 4 p.m. The following telegram, 29 hours in
                            transmission, has been received from the consul general at Canton:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“June 7, 5 p.m. Referring to my telegram of June 5, 3 p.m.
                                    Fighting began about 4:30 p.m. on Saturday and still continues.
                                    All Americans safe so far.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>